<l>ṇaṉaveṉ puḷḷimuṉ yāvu ñāvum</l>
<l>viṉaiyō raṉaiya veṉmaṉār pulavar</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Scholars say that <foreign xml:lang="ta">y-</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">ñ-</foreign> may stand</l>
<l>as initials of verbs after [words ending]</l>
<l>in the non-vocalized consonants <foreign xml:lang="ta">-ṇ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">-ṉ</foreign>.<note
              place="foot">Both <foreign xml:lang="ta">maṇ yātta</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">maṇ ñātta, poṉ yātta</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta">poṉ ñātta</foreign> are possible.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
